 Trade Union Congress (TUC). Photo: NigeriaBusinessDirectory  He said: “As it stands now, we may be forced to go to the trenches. We remain solidly behind the leadership of the Joint National Public Service Negotiating Council handling the negotiation on behalf of labour.”
 
He urged the Federal Government to act fast and direct its representatives to return to the negotiating table with a more realistic mandate that would be beneficial to workers who have waited for almost a decade to get a salary increase.
 
